cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "Negotiation-Safety Layer (NSL): a first LLM implementation of ex post verifiable disarmament commitments"
message: "If you use this software or its results, please cite it using this metadata."
type: software
authors:
  - given-names: Michael
    family-names: Boozer
    orcid: "https://orcid.org/0009-0003-6725-1373"
repository-code: "https://github.com/MikeBoozer/negotiation-safety-layer"
url: "https://github.com/MikeBoozer/negotiation-safety-layer"
abstract: >-
  Middleware that wraps a delegate AI agent in a strategic negotiation so it
  refuses to reward coercion while still closing good deals and leaves ordinary
  work untouched. Includes an experiment implementing ex post verifiable
  disarmament commitments (Sauerberg & Oesterheld, AAAI 2026) in LLM bargaining
  agents: against a hardball counterparty, coercion rates fell 1.00 -> 0.35 ->
  0.00 across no-commitment / cheap-talk / verifiable arms.
keywords:
  - cooperative AI
  - AI safety
  - safe Pareto improvements
  - verifiable commitments
  - surrogate goals
  - LLM agents
  - bargaining
